cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.PL, cs.CC 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper deals with planning problems and temporal constraints, which are common topics in AI research. 
2. cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) - The paper discusses decidability and complexity results, which are often studied in the context of logic and formal methods. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper involves analyzing the complexity of a problem and exploring different cases, which are typical topics in algorithms research. 
4. cs.PL (Programming Languages) - The paper deals with modeling and representing temporal constraints, which can be relevant in programming language design. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper focuses on the complexity of timeline-based planning, which is a natural fit for the computational complexity sub-category.
